  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nSince Quarkus 3.10 it is possible to use annotations to select an authentication mechanism specific to each Jakarta REST endpoint via `HttpAuthenticationMechanism` (https://quarkus.io/guides/security-authentication-mechanisms#use-annotations-to-enable-path-based-authentication-for-jakarta-rest-endpoints), with the restriction that currently only one `HttpAuthenticationMechanism` annotation can be defined on the same endpoint.\r\n\r\nPlease allow to define multiple `HttpAuthenticationMechanism` annotations on the same endpoint. \r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n_No response_",
